        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Week 4 of "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Summer into AI 2026"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " hosted by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "@advisoryhour"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " — theme: Built on Yesterday."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Side Effect Oracle showed you one drug's FDA adverse event profile. Side Effect Storm loads up to three drugs simultaneously, overlays their adverse reaction profiles on a D3 spider chart, animates 24 months of reporting trends, and then fires Claude extended thinking to reason about dangerous combination risks using 10 million real FAERS reports as its evidence base."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Worth noting alongside this: "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "link",
              "attrs": {
                "href": "https://advisoryhour.substack.com",
                "target": "_blank",
                "rel": "noopener noreferrer nofollow",
                "class": null
              }
            }
          ],
          "text": "Other week-4 entries"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " built on a single data source; Side Effect Storm makes multi-drug comparison the core mechanic and surfaces combination risks that single-drug tools can't see"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How the AI works"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Parallel FDA FAERS fetches"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — for each drug, the API fetches top 15 adverse reactions, a seriousness breakdown (serious vs. not), 24 months of monthly event counts, and label warning text — all in parallel via Promise.all."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "D3 radar chart comparison"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — the union of all three drugs' top-10 reactions becomes the spider chart axes. Each drug gets a colored polygon. Shared reactions where one drug dominates are immediately visible."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "Claude extended thinking for interactions"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " — with 2+ drugs loaded, Claude receives all three full data profiles and uses 8,000 thinking tokens to identify dangerous combinations, shared risk factors, and specific populations at elevated risk. The reasoning streams live."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "textAlign": null,
        "level": 2
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "How to play"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bullet_list",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Enter up to three drug names (or click a quick-pick chip like 'Lipitor + Metformin')."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Click ANALYZE DATA to load the spider chart, severity bars, and trend sparklines."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "With two or more drugs loaded, click "
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "strong"
                    }
                  ],
                  "text": "ANALYZE COMBINATION"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " to stream Claude's extended thinking interaction analysis."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list_item",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "attrs": {
                "textAlign": null
              },
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Try notorious combos: Ambien + Xanax, Adderall + Prozac, or the three worst-in-class drugs from different categories."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
